window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>For two million years, Mars hid an </b><b><i>alien</i></b><b> secret...</b></p> <p><b>...two </b><b><i>hours</i></b><b> ago, an unmanned rover found it.</b></p> <p>Earth scrambles to assemble the first manned mission to the Red Planet, ignoring safety concerns. The A-list astronauts walk away. Is the secret mission doomed?</p> <p>Who will they turn to?</p> <p>Retired astronaut Adam Alston has made mistakes - he can't support his family. When NASA comes knocking for a mission leader, it's a match made in heaven. Does he still have the right stuff to lead a team?</p> <p>As the adventure tumbles toward the secret, the team discovers there's a fine line between hero and villain. Will they reach the secret in time?</p> <p>The clock is ticking.</p> <p>Priced for fun, get your copy today!</p> <p>Now a <i>complete</i>, best-selling series, over 130,000 copies sold!</p> <p>Questions for the author about Red Hope series:</p> <p>Q: Is the Red Hope series hard scifi?</p> <p>A: No. Not at all. It's general scifi with a plot-driven mix of adventure and current-day Mars mystery. You won't need a calculator or a slide rule to enjoy these books.</p> <p>Q: Is the series complete?</p> <p>A: Yes! Blue Hope marks the end of the series and it does it with a solid (but wild) ending. There is no cliff-hanger at the end of Blue Hope.</p> <p>This is the first novel in a two-book series.</p> <p>This first book ends with a mild cliffhanger.</p> <p>The final novel in this series, <i>Blue Hope</i>, is available now.</p>"; 
